benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid deletion of tags scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC18) with 204 responses and tags removed
Concurrency/Performance handling (TC17) with multiple simultaneous requests
TagDef parameter variations and additional query parameter handling (TC01, TC02, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC09, TC13, TC14, TC16)
Input validation and error handling coverage (invalid IDs, missing header, invalid token, service unavailable, malformed tagDef, large tagDef sets, and dangerous headers)
gaps: Soft deletes semantics are not covered (no tests asserting a soft-delete behavior or flag on the invoice item tags)
recommendations: Add a dedicated test to verify soft-delete semantics if applicable
Add explicit authorization tests for DELETE to cover authentication/authorization scenarios independently of GET guidelines
Enhance concurrency tests with race-condition scenarios on the same resource
Add boundary tests for very large tagDef lists to verify system limits and behavior (e.g., 413)
